 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.24","title":"[audit][service] Deduplicate StaticList endpoints to preserve set semantics","description":"StaticList currently replays duplicate endpoints verbatim on first poll and from endpoints(), which violates Discover's set-oriented semantics and can double-insert the same endpoint into downstream balancers/pools. Deduplicate while preserving deterministic first-seen order, add targeted regression coverage, and validate with rch-offloaded cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteCliff","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:06:20.028224339Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:04:08.685485399Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:04:04.453395535Z","close_reason":"Completed: deduplicated StaticList endpoint set semantics with focused regressions and rch-backed check/clippy/test validation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.24","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:06:20.028224339Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2456,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.24","author":"WhiteCliff","text":"Validation update: src/service/discover.rs patch is landed. rch-targeted lib cargo check and clippy passed remotely, rustfmt passed locally, and the earlier tests-check failure was infra-only (worker no-space on /tmp). One focused rch regression test retry was launched but the wrapper never surfaced a final pass/fail line, so I have not overclaimed targeted test success yet.","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:49:59Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.240","title":"[audit][service] Make LoadBalancedFuture fail closed after terminal completion","description":"src/service/load_balance.rs decrements the chosen backend's load metric when LoadBalancedFuture first completes, but the wrapper never records a terminal Done state. A second poll re-enters the already-completed inner future instead of failing closed, so misuse can re-trigger inner post-completion behavior while the load metric has already been discharged. Add explicit terminal-state tracking, return a typed LoadBalanceError on repoll, preserve one-time load decrement semantics on completion/drop, add focused regressions for success and error paths, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","notes":"Detected an active same-file reservation conflict on src/service/load_balance.rs from PurpleMoose immediately after claim. Yielding that lane instead of colliding and pivoting to an unclaimed combinator audit slice.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:44:36.731992900Z","created_by":"LilacBay","updated_at":"2026-03-12T06:12:06.508262015Z","closed_at":"2026-03-12T06:12:06.508236388Z","close_reason":"Superseded by active same-surface audit beads asupersync-1qfd0.241 and asupersync-1qfd0.244 after original reservation conflict","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","load-balance","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.240","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:44:36.731992900Z","created_by":"LilacBay","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
