 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.242","title":"[audit][transport] Make SymbolSink helper futures fail closed after terminal completion","description":"src/transport/sink.rs exposes public helper futures (SendFuture, SendAllFuture, FlushFuture, CloseFuture) that can be polled again after returning Poll::Ready. Today repeated polls either keep returning success (SendFuture) or re-drive sink operations (SendAllFuture, FlushFuture, CloseFuture) instead of failing closed on terminal misuse. Add explicit done-state tracking, surface a typed transport sink error for post-completion polls, add focused regressions, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"RedBeacon","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:45:46.056354890Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T05:46:23.922910866Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.242","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:45:46.056354890Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.243","title":"[audit][stream] Make Count/Any/All/ForEach terminal futures idempotent on repoll","description":"src/stream/count.rs, src/stream/any_all.rs, and src/stream/for_each.rs currently assert/panic when their terminal futures are polled after completion, even though their outputs are naturally idempotent (usize, bool, and ()). Tighten these combinators so a second poll after Ready does not panic, does not re-enter the upstream stream, and does not replay side effects. Preserve first-completion semantics and add focused regressions for Count, Any, All, ForEach, and ForEachAsync repoll behavior. Validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilentPeak","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-12T05:46:05.408187832Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T06:02:08.969108131Z","closed_at":"2026-03-12T06:02:08.139753054Z","close_reason":"Completed; current-snapshot validation blocked by unrelated compile errors outside stream repoll lane","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.243","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:46:05.408187832Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.244","title":"[audit][service] Return NoReadyBackends when strategy cannot select from non-empty backend set","description":"In src/service/load_balance.rs::LoadBalancer::call_balanced, strategy.pick(&loads) returning None is currently mapped to LoadBalanceError::NoBackends even when backend_handles is non-empty (e.g., Weighted strategy with all-zero weights). This misclassifies selection exhaustion as topology absence and weakens diagnostics/triage. Update call_balanced to return LoadBalanceError::NoReadyBackends when the backend set is non-empty but strategy cannot select a candidate, add focused deterministic regressions, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","notes":"Implemented scoped fix in src/service/load_balance.rs: strategy.pick(&loads)==None now maps to LoadBalanceError::NoReadyBackends (not NoBackends) when backend set is non-empty. Added focused regression lb_call_balanced_reports_no_ready_when_strategy_declines_all_backends (Weighted zero-weight case). Validation via rch: cargo fmt --check reports broad pre-existing workspace formatting drift; cargo check --all-targets completed successfully once (remote) then later runs hit moving unrelated frontiers in src/stream/debounce.rs; cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings fails on unrelated pre-existing manual_assert lints in src/stream/{any_all,count,for_each}. Targeted load_balance lib test is currently blocked by unrelated compile errors in src/transport/stream.rs and src/stream/debounce.rs on the shared snapshot.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PearlBarn","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:46:41.524830432Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T06:01:50.723578232Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.244","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:46:41.524830432Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.244","title":"[audit][service] Return NoReadyBackends when strategy cannot select from non-empty backend set","description":"In src/service/load_balance.rs::LoadBalancer::call_balanced, strategy.pick(&loads) returning None is currently mapped to LoadBalanceError::NoBackends even when backend_handles is non-empty (e.g., Weighted strategy with all-zero weights). This misclassifies selection exhaustion as topology absence and weakens diagnostics/triage. Update call_balanced to return LoadBalanceError::NoReadyBackends when the backend set is non-empty but strategy cannot select a candidate, add focused deterministic regressions, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","notes":"[2026-03-12 BlackSparrow] Taking over stale bead for closure validation on current snapshot. Existing src/service/load_balance.rs already maps strategy.pick(&loads)==None to LoadBalanceError::NoReadyBackends and includes focused regression lb_call_balanced_reports_no_ready_when_strategy_declines_all_backends; proceeding with targeted rch-backed validation and closure if green.\n\n[2026-03-12 BlackSparrow] Validation completed via rch-backed targeted lanes on current snapshot: (1) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_blacksparrow_244_libtest_v1 cargo test -p asupersync --lib lb_call_balanced_reports_no_ready_when_strategy_declines_all_backends -- --nocapture (PASS); (2) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_blacksparrow_244_libtest_v1 cargo check -p asupersync --lib --message-format short (PASS); (3) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_blacksparrow_244_libtest_v1 cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings (PASS); (4) rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/service/load_balance.rs (PASS). No additional code edits were required in this takeover pass because the scoped fix and focused regression were already present and passing.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BlackSparrow","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:46:41.524830432Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T14:51:14.587100764Z","closed_at":"2026-03-12T14:51:14.587074265Z","close_reason":"Validated NoReadyBackends mapping + focused regression; no further code changes required.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.244","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:46:41.524830432Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.245","title":"[audit][stream] Make Fold/Try* terminal repolls idempotent","description":"Fold in src/stream/fold.rs and the terminal futures in src/stream/try_stream.rs (TryCollect, TryFold, TryForEach) currently panic on post-completion repolls via assert/expect state checks. Harden them so repolling after terminal completion is idempotent, does not repoll upstream streams, and does not replay user-visible side effects. Add focused regressions covering success and error terminal paths, then validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SwiftBadger","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-12T05:49:38.441965520Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T05:56:29.404855834Z","closed_at":"2026-03-12T05:56:27.574591470Z","close_reason":"Stale duplicate: Fold/TryFold already fail closed before upstream repoll; full terminal replay is not a sound generic contract here","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.245","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:49:38.441965520Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.246","title":"[audit][service] Close Buffer after synchronous inner call panic to avoid wedged readiness","description":"src/service/buffer.rs leaves the shared inner service logically reserved if inner.call(req) panics after poll_ready succeeded. PendingGuard releases outer capacity, but the shared inner service can stay wedged, so later poll_ready calls may authorize new work that then hangs forever in WaitingForReady. Harden BufferFuture so a synchronous inner call panic fail-closes the shared buffer before unwinding, add focused regressions proving the service does not wedge, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","notes":"Implemented in src/service/buffer.rs: introduced close_shared_buffer() and now catch synchronous panics from the shared inner service during BufferFuture::poll when calling inner.poll_ready(...) or inner.call(req). On either panic path, the shared buffer is marked closed, waiters are woken, pending capacity is released via PendingGuard, and the panic is resumed so the offending caller still observes the unwind. Added focused regressions inner_poll_ready_panic_closes_buffer_and_future and inner_call_panic_closes_buffer_and_prevents_wedged_readiness. Validation attempted via rch only: (1) rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync panic_closes_buffer -- --nocapture failed on unrelated current-snapshot compile blockers outside this lane: src/stream/debounce.rs E0502 and src/transport/stream.rs missing SymbolSinkExt import / E0282; (2) rch exec -- cargo fmt --check reports broad pre-existing workspace formatting drift outside this bead, though rustfmt was applied to src/service/buffer.rs locally; (3) rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets and rch exec -- cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings both hit unstable rch worker/build-lock behavior after remote timeout fallback, so no additional lane-specific failures were observed beyond the shared compile frontiers already seen in targeted cargo test. Keeping bead in_progress pending frontier-clear revalidation.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SwiftBadger","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-12T05:56:51.682589413Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T06:12:39.232499006Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.246","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T05:56:51.682589413Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.247","title":"[compile][stream] Fix Debounce pending-item borrow regression in quiet-period flush","description":"Current HEAD has an incomplete local fix in src/stream/debounce.rs: the quiet-period flush path borrows pending.as_ref() immutably via received_at and then calls pending.take() before that borrow ends, triggering E0502 in cargo check. Restructure the elapsed/flush logic so debounce can move the buffered item without overlapping borrows, preserve the intended semantics of the in-tree take-if-present hardening, and rerun rch-backed library validation to confirm the debounce frontier is cleared while leaving unrelated active frontiers untouched.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"LilacBay","created_at":"2026-03-12T06:02:43.428324990Z","created_by":"LilacBay","updated_at":"2026-03-12T11:42:32.414694314Z","closed_at":"2026-03-12T11:42:32.414675098Z","close_reason":"Current tree already satisfies the bead contract; WildRidge revalidated the landed debounce borrow-fix in src/stream/debounce.rs (commit 06343b0f) with rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-wildridge-debounce-check cargo check -p asupersync --lib. Existing March 12 source/tests show the old E0502 frontier is stale, so no code change was required in this pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","compile","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.247","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T06:02:43.428324990Z","created_by":"LilacBay","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
