 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.250","title":"[audit][service] Make FilterFuture fail closed after terminal completion","description":"src/service/filter.rs currently returns FilterFuture::{NotReady, Rejected, Inner} without any terminal done-state tracking. NotReady and Rejected can be polled repeatedly forever, and once Inner returns Poll::Ready a second poll re-enters the completed inner future instead of failing closed. Add explicit terminal-state handling, surface a typed FilterError for post-completion misuse, preserve the existing readiness-window semantics for accepted vs rejected calls, add focused regressions for success/rejected/not-ready completion paths, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldLynx","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-12T11:31:25.947653826Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T11:31:25.947653826Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.250","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T11:31:25.947653826Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.251","title":"[audit][service] Make Steer reject invalid picker indexes instead of modulo-wrapping","description":"src/service/steer.rs currently computes the selected backend as picker(req) % services.len(), so an out-of-range picker result silently wraps to some other backend instead of failing closed. That hides router bugs and can send requests to the wrong service. Replace modulo wrapping with a typed invalid-route failure, preserve normal successful routing for in-range selections, add focused regressions proving out-of-range picks do not dispatch to any backend, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"DarkGlen","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-12T11:34:56.362439997Z","created_by":"DarkGlen","updated_at":"2026-03-12T11:34:56.362439997Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.251","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T11:34:56.362439997Z","created_by":"DarkGlen"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.252","title":"[compile][service] Fix FilterFuture::inner test type inference regression (E0282)","description":"rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets currently fails with E0282 in src/service/filter.rs:699 (FilterFuture::inner(std::future::ready(Ok(42))) cannot infer Result error type in lib tests). Scope: make the test explicit and deterministic (or equivalent API-typed helper), keep behavior unchanged, add/adjust focused assertions if needed, then validate using rch-backed check/test for touched surface.","notes":"2026-03-12 MistyLynx: Revalidated this compile bead on current snapshot. src/service/filter.rs already carries explicit type annotation in filter_future_inner_debug (FilterFuture<std::future::Ready<Result<i32, ()>>>) at lines 648-650, so E0282 reproduction no longer occurs. Remote validation (rch): cargo check -p asupersync --lib (pass), cargo check --all-targets (pass). No additional code changes required in this lane.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"MistyLynx","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-12T11:39:07.278101505Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T12:30:08.473718252Z","closed_at":"2026-03-12T12:30:08.473695960Z","close_reason":"Resolved on current snapshot (E0282 no longer reproducible)","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","compile","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.252","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T11:39:07.278101505Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.253","title":"[audit][sync] Remove notify_one lock-scope clippy suppression while preserving lost-wakeup safety","description":"notify_one in src/sync/notify.rs currently relies on #[allow(clippy::significant_drop_tightening)] to keep lock scope and lost-wakeup semantics aligned. Refactor notify_one to preserve the same behavior (no lost wakeups, wake outside lock) without requiring suppression, then run targeted validation for notify tests via rch-backed cargo commands.","notes":"Patched src/sync/notify.rs::Notify::notify_one to remove #[allow(clippy::significant_drop_tightening)] while preserving lost-wakeup safety: waiter lock is held through stored_notifications increment when no waiter is found, and wake remains outside the lock when waiter exists. Validation via rch only: (1) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_hazy_notify_test cargo test -p asupersync notify_one_ -- --nocapture surfaced unrelated workspace compile frontier (non-exhaustive matches for channel::mpsc::{SendError,RecvError}::PolledAfterCompletion across actor/gen_server/http/session/messaging/stream modules); (2) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_hazy_check_all_v2 cargo check --all-targets hit same unrelated E0004 frontier; (3) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_hazy_clippy_all_v2 cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings hit same unrelated E0004 frontier; (4) rch exec -- cargo fmt --check fails on pre-existing broad formatting drift in many unrelated files. Scoped notify.rs change remains isolated.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"HazyWaterfall","created_at":"2026-03-12T11:40:24.592371425Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T11:54:35.048917789Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","clippy","sync"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.253","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T11:40:24.592371425Z","created_by":"ubu