+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.253","title":"[audit][sync] Remove notify_one lock-scope clippy suppression while preserving lost-wakeup safety","description":"notify_one in src/sync/notify.rs currently relies on #[allow(clippy::significant_drop_tightening)] to keep lock scope and lost-wakeup semantics aligned. Refactor notify_one to preserve the same behavior (no lost wakeups, wake outside lock) without requiring suppression, then run targeted validation for notify tests via rch-backed cargo commands.","notes":"[2026-03-12 BlackSparrow] Taking over stale bead. Current src/sync/notify.rs still has #[allow(clippy::significant_drop_tightening)] on Notify::notify_one; implementing lock-scope-safe refactor that preserves lost-wakeup semantics while removing suppression, then revalidating via rch-backed targeted lanes.\n\n[2026-03-12 BlackSparrow] Implemented scoped refactor in src/sync/notify.rs::Notify::notify_one: removed clippy suppression; converted to branch-local lock handling that (a) finds/takes waiter waker under lock, (b) stores notification token under lock when no waiter exists, and (c) wakes outside lock. Added explicit guard drops at branch boundaries to satisfy clippy while preserving lost-wakeup safety requirements.\n\nValidation completed via rch-backed targeted lanes on current snapshot: (1) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_blacksparrow_253_lib_v1 cargo test -p asupersync --lib notify_one_ -- --nocapture (PASS, 8 tests); (2) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_blacksparrow_253_lib_v1 cargo check -p asupersync --lib --message-format short (PASS); (3) rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_blacksparrow_253_lib_v1 cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings (PASS); (4) rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/sync/notify.rs (PASS).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BlackSparrow","created_at":"2026-03-12T11:40:24.592371425Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T15:06:24.982635850Z","closed_at":"2026-03-12T15: